/bin/bash -lc "nl -ba content/papers/search.md | sed -n '1,90p;500,530p'" in /home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive succeeded in 51ms:
     1	---
     2	title: "Entropy and Search Theory"
     3	author: ["E.T. Jaynes"]
     4	year: 1985
     5	---
     6	## Introduction
     7	A recent article by Pierce[^pierce1978] has brought search theory to the
     8	attention of workers in related fields which also use statistical
     9	theory. In recounting history, he noted that early workers tried to
    10	relate detection probability $p_D$ and search effort to the posterior
    11	entropy $H_{ND}$ conditional on nondetection \[Eq. (4) below\] or to the
    12	\"expected posterior entropy\" $H_E = p_D H_D + (1-p_D) H_{ND}$,
    13	discovered quickly that no general relation exists; and concluded that
    14	information theory has no useful connection with search theory.
    15	
    16	As Pierce stated: \"These negative findings had a clearly inhibiting
    17	effect on research, and relatively little effort has been devoted to the
    18	connections between information and search for the past fifteen years.
